name: **_Ceann Sibéal go Ceann Bhréanain_**
description:
Ceann Sibéal go Ceann Bhréanain Q309-060 to Q528-173 Sheet 70 28km of stunning cliffs, broken only by the 2km width of Smerwick Harbour, the waystop at Brandon Creek, and the 1km width of Sauce Creek. It is impossible and pointless to try to land elsewhere. Paddle close to the cliff line to appreciate the waterfalls, caves, arches, and many ‘islands’ of cliff, which merge with the background. The cliffs of the Three Sisters (Triúr Deirfiúir) and Sybil Point at the SW part of the section is a must. Tides

Sybil Point to Brandon Point
Direction Time Speed
NE 4:50 after Galway HW 3kn
SW 1:30 before Galway HW 3kn

Smerwick Harbour
